<subSubSection pageId="85" pageNumber="362" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="85.[180,1387,3054,3365]" pageId="85" pageNumber="364">
Taxonomy. 
<taxonomicName authority="Thomas, 1893" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1893" box="[348,749,3054,3087]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Neotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="85" pageNumber="364" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lepida">Neotoma lepida Thomas, 1893</taxonomicName>
, “Utah.” Restricted by E. A. Goldman in 1932 to “somewhere on ‘Simpson’s route’ between Camp Floyd [= Fairfield] (a few miles west of Utah Lake), Utah, and Carson City, Nevada,” USA.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="85" pageNumber="362" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="85.[180,1387,3054,3365]" pageId="85" pageNumber="364">
During taxonomic revision of N. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1893" box="[644,718,3171,3204]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Neotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="85" pageNumber="364" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lepida">lepida</taxonomicName>
group, many of formerly recognized subspecies of N. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1893" box="[261,335,3211,3244]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Neotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="85" pageNumber="364" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lepida">lepida</taxonomicName>
were subsumed into N. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Merriam" authorityYear="1887" box="[676,766,3211,3244]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Neotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="85" pageNumber="364" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bryanti">bryanti</taxonomicName>
or N. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Goldman" authorityYear="1927" box="[855,922,3211,3244]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Neotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="85" pageNumber="364" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="devia">devia</taxonomicName>
. Three subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
